/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&nbs=\r\np;the invocation is being made to pitru devataas to come and accept the off=\r\nerings prepared by us and then favour us by providing health and blessings =\r\nfree from sin - seems to be a bribe being made to pitru devataas, certainly=\r\n not. the request is to bestow sinless peace and tranquility upon us, the w=\r\nord\n rapaH is a synonymn for sin and arapaH is opposite of that i.e. sinles=\r\ns. the request is to grant peace and tranquility that is sinless upon us (n=\r\naH shaM yoH arapaH dadhaata). One will attain sinless peace when there is &quot;=\r\nin-action in action&quot; and that is sacrifice/yaGYa/pitru kaarya, one can atta=\r\nin peace (temporary) by &quot;no-action&quot; but that is sinful, and sacrifices such=\r\n as yaGYa/pitru kaarya are ones dharma (actually a RRiNa), hence the requis=\r\nition is for a dharmic cause - to help us (uuti) by providing sinless peace=\r\n (arapaH - shaM), arapaH also means free from disease (i.e health) so the r=\r\nequisition can also be translated as - to help us by providing auspicious b=\r\nlessing and health (connected to earlier rik RV10.015.03 - where the invoka=\r\ntion was for progeny &nbsp;- napaataM &nbsp;to continue with yaGYa - viShNo=\r\nH)&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&nbsp; references: Vedic reader by A.A. MacDone=\r\nll, Monier Williams and Mac Donell dictionaries via Mudgala Kosha, Roots\n a=\r\nnd Verb-Forms by W.D. Whitney, Vedic Grammar by AA MacDonell, all these ref=\r\nerences are freely available on the internet.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Rega=\r\nrds,&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;sarma.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;\n\n\n    &lt;/div&gt;\n     \n\n\n\n \n=\r\n\n\n\n\n\n&lt;/div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/body&gt;&lt;/html&gt;\r\n---435270448-1671952794-1316249062=:8547--\r\n\n"}}